  "local_port": 49498,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "Keeping your Instagram account private from Facebook friends and contacts involves adjusting both your Instagram and Facebook settings to limit data sharing and visibility. Here's a comprehensive step-by-step guide to help you achieve this:\n\n### 1. **Disconnect Instagram from Facebook**\n\nIf your Instagram account is linked to your Facebook account, disconnecting them can prevent Facebook contacts from finding you on Instagram.\n\n**On Instagram App:**\n\n1. **Open Instagram:** Launch the Instagram app on your mobile device.\n2. **Go to Profile:** Tap on your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n3. **Access Settings:** Tap the three horizontal lines (\u22ee) in the top right corner, then select **Settings**.\n4. **Account Center:** Scroll down and tap on **Account Center**.\n5. **Accounts & Profiles:** Here, you can see the accounts linked to Instagram. Tap **Accounts & profiles**.\n6. **Remove Facebook Account:** Select your Facebook account and choose **Remove from Account Center**.\n\n**On Instagram Web:**\n\n1. **Log In:** Visit [Instagram.com](https://www.instagram.com/) and log into your account.\n2. **Go to Settings:** Click on your profile picture in the top right, select **Settings**.\n3. **Account Center:** Look for **Account Center** in the settings.\n4. **Disconnect Facebook:** Follow the prompts to remove your Facebook account from the Account Center.\n\n### 2. **Adjust Instagram Privacy Settings**\n\nEnsure that your Instagram account is set to private, limiting visibility to only approved followers.\n\n1. **Open Instagram:** Launch the app and go to your profile.\n2. **Access Settings:** Tap the three horizontal lines (\u22ee) > **Settings**.\n3. **Privacy:** Select **Privacy**.\n4. **Private Account:** Toggle on **Private Account**. This ensures only people you approve can see your posts and stories.\n\n### 3. **Limit Who Can Discover Your Instagram Through Facebook**\n\nEven after disconnecting, some information might still be shared. To further limit discovery:\n\n1. **Open Instagram Settings:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Privacy** > **Connections**.\n2. **Suggested Accounts:** Disable **Similar Account Suggestions** to prevent Instagram from suggesting your profile to Facebook friends.\n3. **Story Sharing:** Under **Privacy**, review **Story** settings to control who can share your stories or see your story status.\n\n### 4. **Manage Contacts and Search Settings**\n\nTo prevent your Facebook contacts from finding you on Instagram:\n\n1. **Contacts Syncing:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Account** > **Contacts Syncing**.\n   - Ensure that **Connect Contacts** is turned off.\n\n2. **Profile Privacy in Facebook:**\n   - On Facebook, ensure your contact information (like phone number or email) is not publicly visible.\n   - Go to **Settings & Privacy** > **Settings** > **Privacy** > **How People Find and Contact You**.\n   - Adjust settings to limit who can look you up using your email or phone number.\n\n### 5. **Remove Existing Facebook Friends from Instagram**\n\nIf some of your Facebook friends are already following you on Instagram:\n\n1. **Remove Followers:**\n   - Go to your profile and tap on your followers list.\n   - Find the Facebook friends you want to remove.\n   - Tap the **Remove** button next to their names.\n\n2. **Block Specific Users:**\n   - Visit the profile of the user you want to block.\n   - Tap the three dots (\u22ee) in the top right corner.\n   - Select **Block** and confirm.\n\n### 6. **Review Third-Party App Permissions**\n\nEnsure that third-party apps connected to your Instagram or Facebook accounts aren't sharing your information inadvertently.\n\n1. **On Instagram:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Apps and Websites**.\n   - Review and remove any apps you don't recognize or no longer use.\n\n2. **On Facebook:**\n   - Go to **Settings & Privacy** > **Settings** > **Apps and Websites**.\n   - Manage and remove unnecessary app permissions.\n\n### 7. **Regularly Monitor Your Privacy Settings**\n\nSocial media platforms frequently update their privacy policies and settings. Regularly review both Instagram and Facebook privacy settings to ensure they align with your privacy preferences.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Use Different Usernames:** Consider using a different username on Instagram that isn't linked to your Facebook name to make it harder for friends to find you.\n  \n- **Be Cautious with Public Information:** Avoid sharing identifiable information in your bio, posts, or stories that could link back to your Facebook profile.\n\nBy following these steps, you can significantly enhance the privacy of your Instagram account and limit visibility from your Facebook friends and contacts.",
